# openehr-bmm – Project Context

- **What it is**: Opinionated PHP library implementing the openEHR Basic Meta-Model (BMM 2.4), mostly an intermediate representation of P_BMM specifications. Composer-installable library, not an application.
- **Authoritative docs**:
  - **AGENTS.md** – layout, ownership, standards (PSR-12, PHPStan, PHPUnit), escalation, triage. Primary reference for agents.
  - **README.md** – setup, Composer scripts, release process.
  - **CLAUDE.md** – Claude Code entrypoint; defers to AGENTS.md and points at Cursor rules under `.cursor/rules/`.
  - **`.cursor/rules/commit-messages.mdc`** – commit messages (including AI-generated): conventional `type: imperative` subject per AGENTS.md; hint `conventional commit, <72 chars, feat/refactor/fix`.

## Layout

| Path | Purpose |
|------|--------|
| `src/` | Library source; PSR-4 namespace `Cadasto\OpenEHR\BMM\` from `composer.json`. |
| `src/Model/` | BMM model classes: schemas, packages, classes, properties, types, functions, enumerations. |
| `src/Helper/` | Collection and collectable helpers for typed object collections. |
| `tests/` | Tests **and** tool config: `phpunit.xml`, `phpstan.neon`, `phpcs.xml`, `rector.php`, optional `phpstan-baseline.neon`. |
| `tests/resources/` | BMM JSON test fixtures (`openehr_base_1.3.0.bmm.json`, `openehr_rm_1.2.0.bmm.json`). |
| `docs/` | Project documentation. Place any new docs here. |
| `.github/workflows/` | CI (lint, CS, PHPStan, tests) and release on version tags. |

## Running commands

- **Composer, PHP, PHPUnit, PHPStan, PHPCS**: run **inside the dev container** only. From repo root: **`make install`**, **`make ci`**, or `docker compose -f .docker/docker-compose.yml run --rm app composer …`. See the [Makefile](../../Makefile).
- **Do not** rely on host `composer` / `php` being installed; agents should default to **`make …`** or the `docker compose` line above.

- **Commits**: Follow **`commit-messages.mdc`** and **AGENTS.md** for every suggestion (including the commit message UI). Same hint: `conventional commit, <72 chars, feat/refactor/fix`.

When in doubt, follow AGENTS.md for standards and README for commands and setup.
